==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fleshy
<hw>Flesh"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Fleshier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Fleshiest</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</amorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Full of,
or composed of, flesh; plump; corpulent; fat; gross.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The sole of his foot is fleshy.</q> <rj><qau>Ray.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Human.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Fleshy</xex> tabernacle.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Composed of firm pulp; succulent;
<as>as, the houseleek, cactus, and agave are <ex>fleshy</ex>
plants</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flet</ent>⟦br⟧
